<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,581,1074]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,581,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. BL 
<number box="[396,448,582,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="4.1">4.10</number>
, PL 
<number box="[501,553,581,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.5">1.50</number>
, PW 
<number box="[614,666,582,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.37">1.37</number>
. Female. BL 
<number box="[818,870,582,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="4.4">4.40</number>
, PL 
<number box="[922,973,581,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.55">1.55</number>
, PW 
<number box="[1036,1088,581,606]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1.5">1.50</number>
. General body color brownish. Pleura and abdominal sternites covered by rounded punctations without setae. Anterior lobe of pronotum with a pair of whitish to pale yellow maculae. Forewing with a basal macula, starting from humeral angle and passing posterior margin of pronotum, convergent on distal half; on the sides of this macula, between radial and cubital vein, another small rounded white macula; pruinose areas between wing cells; on distal half, another pale white macula, with slightly concave posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[691,771,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1475,1497]" captionTargetBox="[302,1288,208,1449]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[296,1291,195,1453]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Dorsal view, (A) Paravelia foveata, (B) P. lanemeloi (paratype), (C) P. manausana, (D) P. nieseri (holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285798/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number box="[743,771,762,786]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Male proctiger without dorsal elevation. Paramere (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1857,1879]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,488,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[181,1405,481,1836]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Lateral view of genital capsule of male, (A) Paravelia bullialata, (B) P. capillata, (C) apex of paramere of P. capillata in frontal view, (D) P. capixaba, (E) P. conata, (F) P. dilatata, (G) P. foveata, (H) P. itatiayana, (I) P. lanemeloi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285797/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,179,797,822]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
G) medially narrow, with apex less rounded than that illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus" box="[934,1347,797,822]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (1984 b) Notes on Neotropical Veliidae (Hemiptera) IX: additional new species of Paravelia from South America. Amazoniana, 8, 497 - 504." type="journal article" year="1984" yearSuffix="b">
Polhemus &amp; Polhemus (
<number box="[1206,1266,797,822]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1984.0">1984</number>
b: 
<number box="[1292,1338,797,822]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="504.0">504</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,581,1074]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,833,858]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Discussion.</emphasis>
Described from the macropterous form and so far known only from the type-locality, in Amazonas State, 
<collectingCountry box="[220,292,869,894]" name="Brazil" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This species, like 
<taxonomicName box="[502,662,870,893]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amapaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[502,662,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P. amapaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[669,758,869,894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[669,758,869,894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[772,849,870,893]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anta">
<emphasis box="[772,849,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P. anta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[863,983,869,893]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[863,983,869,893]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P. bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[990,1079,869,894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[990,1079,869,894]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1208,869,893]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata">
<emphasis box="[1093,1208,869,893]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1429,869,893]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungerfordi">
<emphasis box="[1269,1429,869,893]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P. hungerfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has the thorax and abdomen covered by rounded or oval punctations. However, it can be easily differentiated from those by the pattern of maculae on anterior lobe of pronotum and on the forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1171,941,966]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1475,1497]" captionTargetBox="[302,1288,208,1449]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[296,1291,195,1453]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Dorsal view, (A) Paravelia foveata, (B) P. lanemeloi (paratype), (C) P. manausana, (D) P. nieseri (holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285798/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number box="[1142,1171,942,966]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
